For both `Rehydrate<T>()` (line 44) and `RehydrateAsync<T>()` (line 82), they call `IsResource<T>()` and `new GenericOperationSource<T>()`. `GenericOperationSource<T>` needs `PublicConstructors | NonPublicConstructors` on T. So these callers need the superset. Change:
